#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:2
msgid "Text Replace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:4
msgid ""
"Open the Search and replace window with +Ctrl+ +K+ and enter the word or "
"expression you wish to replace in the *Search for* box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:7
msgid ""
"Then click on *Search* button to display all the corresponding "
"occurrences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:10
msgid ""
"Enter the new word or phrase (regular expressions are not supported) in "
"the *Replace with* box, then click one of the following options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:13
msgid ""
"**Replace All:** operates replacement of all occurrences (after "
"displaying a confirmation window where the number of occurrences is "
"shown)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:17
msgid ""
"**Replace:** operates a \"one by one\" replacement, by the mean of "
"buttons in the **header of the Editor pane**. Click *Replace Next* or "
"*Skip*, then end the replacement session with *Finish*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:21
msgid "**Close:** close the window without any change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:24
msgid "Search options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:26
msgid ""
"Search options are similar to the ones displayed in `Search window "
"<#windows.textsearch>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:29
msgid ""
"Except one: check **Untranslated** in order to operate Search and replace"
" also on segments that have not been translated yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_TextReplace.rst:32
msgid ""
"To make it possible (although Search and replace operates only on "
"memory), OmegaT will copy the source segment to the target segment before"
" the replace operation occurs. If no replacement is done to a given "
"segment, the target segment will be “emptied”, i.e., it will remain "
"untranslated."
msgstr ""

